      "message": "This affects `cipd` command, not just `vpython`. Setting CIPD_SERVICE_URL this way will unconditionally and silently override the service URL, even if one was passed explicitly via `cipd -service-url ...` or as `$ServiceURL` directive in an ensure file. This is not consistent with how other CIPD env vars are treated. The consistent behavior would be to pick up CIPD_SERVICE_URL only if `-service-url` flag is absent and the ensure file doesn\u0027t have `$ServiceURL`. This would be more complicated to implement (search for \"ServiceURL\" in https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/cipd/client/cli/main.go?q\u003dcli%2Fmain.go\u0026ss\u003dchromium).\n\nSo please either implement the logic above, or at least rename the env var to CIPD_OVERRIDE_SERVICE_URL to indicate that it stomps over any other way to set the service URL.\n\nEither way, please document the env var in https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/cipd/client/cli/main.go;l\u003d3297?q\u003dcli%2Fmain.go\u0026ss\u003dchromium",
